<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-1A859B8C-9A8A-41DD-B7FF-C5198776B3C1" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-1A859B8C-9A8A-41DD-B7FF-C5198776B3C1" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 How to remove the Hard Disk Drive</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Dis-assembly</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140852-B298" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note id="M140852-ATN299" type="important" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">After you open the cover, use antistatic precautions to prevent damage to the hardware. See 
<xref keyref="SAFEUSE" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-90C8F720-CF47-4BFD-B0A4-AF5208D41820.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>Instructions for safe use (Technician)</xref> 
</p></note><note id="M140852-CAN301" type="caution" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The processor and heat sink assembly can get extremely hot. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Do not touch it. 
</p></note></section><prereq id="PREREQ_86C8C373EC914441A2AB4B5AAAE49162" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Power off the system</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On the operator panel, tap on the [System] icon on the right. Tap on [Power management]. Tap on [Power off]. The system shuts down. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Switch off the power supply</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After the system has shut down, loosen the 2 screws of the media output lower cover. Lift and remove the cover. Switch the power switch to the 'off' position. 
</p></li><li id="LI_D9426E44E0874AE3B00AD66D8B995A23" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the Windows controller. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref keyref="20DISA-CONTROLLER" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A1843CF6-5762-4FEC-9CF3-EF86B7960A0F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 How to remove the Windows controller (11pba04)</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">To save time: it is possible to leave the Windows controller in the printer. 
</p></li><li id="LI_3751EE2924394BEF8E4707B8704DA7AE" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<xref keyref="20DISA-COVERS" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-3827EE63-CD4E-4A86-8757-DBB096FA2046.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>11 How to open and close the covers of the Windows controller</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="SECTION_BC4C9DB1335C400D8CFB6D62C2406122" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-87FD6A7E-D324-4C14-88B1-66D778A4FEF3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2501567F-DE8B-415D-AF9F-BE1F01410A05-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2501567F-DE8B-415D-AF9F-BE1F01410A05-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-65AEB892-F67E-4302-B277-2C9022A592AE" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
